      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) used under institutional software QA plan. Version control and regression test suite documented.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 is operated under an FDA-recognized software QA framework. Institutional SOP documents version pinning, regression testing against canonical benchmark cases (lid-driven cavity, backward-facing step), and change-control procedures. No custom solver modifications applied. Gradation 2 requirement satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver verified against ASME V&V 20 benchmark cases; order-of-accuracy confirmed for laminar and turbulent pipe flow.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been independently verified against ASME V&V 20 benchmark suite. Second-order spatial accuracy confirmed via Richardson extrapolation on pipe-flow benchmark (observed order 1.93). No anomalous convergence behavior detected in any CPB operating-point simulation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% on primary QoI (RH index and ΔP). Three-mesh refinement study required.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse 4.2 M, medium 11.7 M, fine 28.4 M hexahedral cells). GCI on RH index: 1.8% (fine-to-medium); GCI on ΔP: 0.9%. Medium mesh selected for production runs as fine mesh GCI < 2% on both QoIs. Exceeds Gradation 2 requirement; Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "In-vitro test conditions (fluid properties, temperature, hematocrit) match simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments conducted using porcine blood at 37 °C ± 0.5 °C, hematocrit 35 ± 2%. CFD simulations use matched fluid properties (density 1055 kg/m³, viscosity Carreau-Yasuda non-Newtonian model fitted to experimental rheology data). Temperature variation effect on viscosity bounded at < 1.5% change in RH. Test condition correspondence confirmed at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (normalized RMS error or equivalent) reported for each validation QoI. Acceptance band ≤ 15% for RH index.",
      "rationale": "Normalized RMS error computed for RH index across 5 operating points: mean 8.7%, maximum 13.2%. Pressure head mean absolute error 3.2%. PIV velocity field normalized RMS 8.4%. All metrics within stated acceptance bands. Comparison methodology follows ASME V&V 20 Section 5 procedures."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs (RH index, ΔP, WSS) directly map to COU decision quantities. Linkage documented.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index is the direct regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate). Pressure head confirms hydraulic performance consistency across operating envelope. Wall shear stress is the mechanistic driver of red blood cell damage in the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model used. All three QoIs are directly decision-relevant for the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same FDA generic pump geometry at overlapping operating conditions with the COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump CAD geometry (v2.1) as the COU simulations. Operating points span 2–6 L/min and 2000–3500 RPM, fully encompassing the 5 COU flow-speed combinations. Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) used for PIV; porcine blood used for hemolysis experiments. Geometric and operational relevance confirmed at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; commercial solver with documented verification record accepted.",
      "rationale": "At Model Risk Level 2 with a commercially verified solver, explicit iterative solver error quantification beyond residual monitoring is not required. Residuals converged to < 1×10⁻⁵ for all equations at all operating points. Gradation 1 accepted per MRL 2 scoping."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst training and simulation SOP documented as sufficient control.",
      "rationale": "Simulations performed by a CFD analyst with > 5 years cardiovascular device simulation experience. Institutional simulation SOP (SOP-CFD-004 Rev 3) governs setup, boundary condition specification, and post-processing. Independent peer review of simulation setup completed by a second qualified analyst. Gradation 1 accepted per MRL 2 scoping."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection justified by literature precedent for similar pump geometries.",
      "rationale": "k-ω SST turbulence model selected based on published literature for centrifugal blood pump CFD (Fraser et al. 2011, Hariharan et al. 2011). Model form uncertainty not formally quantified at MRL 2; sensitivity study across two turbulence models (k-ω SST, realizable k-ε) shows < 4% variation in peak WSS, providing informal bounding. Gradation 1 accepted."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; nominal input values with stated tolerances documented in simulation report.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) specified at nominal values with documented measurement tolerances. Sensitivity to ±5% flow rate and ±2% rotational speed variation evaluated informally as part of the UQ activity for RH index. Formal model input uncertainty propagation not required at MRL 2."
    },
