    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at MRL 2. Three primary validation QoIs (RH index, pressure head, wall shear stress) demonstrate quantitative agreement within acceptance bands. The CFD model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The relative hemolysis index criterion (RH < 1) is satisfied across all five COU operating points with uncertainty bounds confirming robustness. Six factors scoped to Gradation 1 (not-assessed) are appropriate for MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. Credibility assessment team accepts the model for the stated COU.",
